üöÄ DUST Hair Studio - Production Launch Checklist

Environment Variables Setup (Vercel)

Required Environment Variables in Vercel Dashboard:
Go to Vercel Dashboard ‚Üí Your Project ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables

Add these variables:

1. Supabase Variables:
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL (your production Supabase URL)
   - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (your production Supabase anon key)

2. Resend Email Variables:
   - RESEND_API_KEY (your production Resend API key)

3. Square Payment Variables (Optional - for future POS integration):
   - SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN (your PRODUCTION Square Access Token)
   - SQUARE_ENVIRONMENT (set to "production")
   - SQUARE_LOCATION_ID (your Square location ID)
   
   Note: Square is used for in-person payments via Square POS after appointments.
   The booking system does NOT require pre-payment - customers book first, pay after service.
   
   Square POS Workflow:
   1. Customer books appointment online (no payment required)
   2. Customer completes service at salon
   3. Stylist takes payment using Square POS
   4. Stylist adds booking ID to transaction note/reference
   5. Admin can manually mark booking as "paid" in dashboard
   6. (Future) Sync Square transactions to auto-update payment status

4. Google Calendar Variables (if using):
   - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID
   - GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET

Set Environment: Select "Production" for all variables
Redeploy: Trigger a new deployment after adding variables

